Articles.Content: ksp 1.1 x64 keeps crashing when i close my laptop (and done put it to sleep) and when i put it to sleep, this happens without fail
This sounds like a support issue. Please provide the information needed for seeking help.

This happens to me, too.

  • KSP version including Windows, Mac, or Linux, 32 or 64-bit, and if it's Steam
    • KSP 1.1 64-bit, Windows x64, Steam
  • A detailed explanation of what happened and what you were trying to accomplish
    • With KSP running, and with the "Pause menu" (i.e. hit esc midflight) up, either put the computer to sleep or switch to a different Windows user. When the computer wakes, or return to the KSP user, KSP shows the crash dialog.
  • A screenshot of your craft or any relevant screens
    • Not relevant - happens with all craft, happens during flight and while in VAB and while at KSC.
  • A .craft file or save files if relevant
    • Not relevant
  • The ouput_log.txt or player.log file KSP creates when it launches and, if applicable, the crash log KSP has generated when the program crashed
    • See below
  • A detailed list of system specifications
    • Intel Core i7-4710HQ, 16GB 1600MHz DDR3 RAM, Nvidia GeForce GTX970M 3GB with Optimus + Intel HD 4600, 256GB SSD
  • Are you running a clean installation, or have you updated and some of your persistence or craft files might be older versions, if so which version(s)
    • Upgraded from 1.0.5, new career game with scratch-built craft
